name: Now You See Me, Now You Don't
description:
[Thank you to the collectors of my artwork in 2021. Your support has provided additional momentum to experiment, produce and share my art in 2022 and onward.]

Now You See Me, Now You Don't, is the first in a series of experiemental works utilizing a webcam/broswer to navigate through an interpolation of ML generated images.

Note: This work requires web browser access to a camera to navigate through the images. Move your head back and forth (left<>right). If the image freezes a browser URL refresh may be required. 

Dimensions variable | Ryan Thompson, January 2022 | RT_Artwork | www.ryanthompson.name
